OL,6,FOn Tuesday, Chancellor Rachel Reeves
OL,7,Fsaid that a review into raising the
OL,8,Fstate pension age is needed to ensure
OL,9,Fthe system is "sustainable and
OL,10,Faffordable".
OL,12,FThe Government review is due to report
OL,13,Fin March 2029 and Ms Reeves said it
OL,14,Fwas "right" to look at the age at
OL,15,Fwhich people can receive the state
OL,16,Fpension as life expectancy increases.
OL,18,FThe state pension age is currently 66,
OL,19,Frising to 67 by 2028 and the
OL,20,FGovernment is legally required to
OL,21,Fperiodically review the age.
